EFF on the red carpet of the State of the Nation Address (SONA) 2019 in Parliament on June 20, 2019 in Cape Town, South Africa. JOHANNESBURG - The South African National Editors' Forum (Sanef) and a group of journalists will square off with the EFF in the Equality Court in Pretoria. Sanef approached the court following intimidation of journalists on social media. WATCH: EFF takes aim at Sanef It wants to stop the EFF leadership from threatening journalist and publishing their personal details on public platforms. Sanef also wants the court to order the EFF to publicly apologise to journalists listed as complainants in this case. READ:Â Sanef takes EFF to Equality court These include News24 editor-in-chief Adriaan Basson, journalists Pauli van Wyk, Ranjeni Munusamy and others. Sanef says it's approached the court to defend the freedom of the media.